            <h2>About Us</h2>
            <p>
                The Volunteers Website is a community-focused platform designed to connect individuals with local problems across districts in Tamil Nadu. It allows users to navigate district-wise pages where predefined problem statements in categories like education, health, disaster relief, and waste management are listed, while also enabling users to submit new problems they observe. Each problem statement includes a "Leader" button, allowing volunteers to step up as leaders by submitting ID proof via a Google Form. Once verified by the respective district admin, the leaderâ€™s contact information, WhatsApp group link, and relevant resources are displayed for others to join and collaborate. The platform promotes transparency through leader verification, ensures ease of access with a user-friendly interface, and fosters grassroots change by empowering individuals, students, NGOs, and institutions to contribute directly to solving real-world issues in their communities.
            </p>
            
        </div>

